<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">EVERCORE TO BUY ISI <span class="divider"> | </span></span> Evercore Partners said on Sunday that it planned to buy Institutional Strategy &#038; Investment in a move intended to bolster its research and trading arm, <b><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/08/03/evercore-to-buy-isi-to-bolster-its-research-and-trading-arm/">Michael J. de la Merced writes in DealBook</a></b>. The deal is aimed at building up a complement to the investment bankâs mainstay advisory operations, Mr. de la Merced adds. By acquiring the company, known as ISI, Evercore is looking to <b>expand its capital markets operations</b>, providing more research and trading offerings for hedge fund clients.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Under the terms of the deal, Evercore will issue up to eight million share equivalents to buy the two businesses, worth about <b>$401 million as of Fridayâs closing price</b>, Mr. de la Merced writes. The ultimate deal price will depend on how well the new business, to be called Evercore ISI Institutional Equities, performs in the five years after closing.</p>
